    • Constructor Detail

      • MendeleySDK

        public MendeleySDK(Context context,
           MendeleySDK.ClientCredentials clientCredentials)
        Obtain a handle to the SDK.

        It is recommended that applications only call this once, and then use the same handle for all requests.

        Parameters:
        context - used for creating the sign-in activity
        clientCredentials - your app's Mendeley ID/secret/Uri, from the registration process

      • MendeleySDK

        public MendeleySDK(Context context,
           MendeleySignInInterface signInCallback,
           MendeleySDK.ClientCredentials clientCredentials)
        Obtain a handle to the SDK.

        It is recommended that applications only call this once, and then use the same handle for all requests.

        Parameters:
        context - used for creating the sign-in activity
        clientCredentials - your app's Mendeley ID/secret/Uri, from the registration process
        signInCallback - used to receive sign in/out events.

      • MendeleySDK

        public MendeleySDK(MendeleySDK.ClientCredentials clientCredentials,
           com.mendeley.api.auth.UserCredentials userCredentials)
        Obtain a handle to the SDK (internal use only).

        Developer applications should not use this constructor; this is only required for unit testing the SDK.
